Examples:

Input: arr[] = [2, 4, 1, 3, 5]
Output: 3
Explanation: The third largest element in the array [2, 4, 1, 3, 5] is 3.
------------>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> CODE
class Solution {
    int thirdLargest(int arr[]) {
        if(arr.length<3){
            return -1;
        }
        int n=arr.length;
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        return arr[n-3];
    }
}
